photo.description: In the Piazza Navona. The Fountain of the Four Rivers was designed by Gian Lorenzo Bernini in 1651, gaining him the admiration and protection of Pope Innocent X. It shows the main rivers of the the four then known continents: the Danube in Europe; the Ganges in Asia; the Nile in Africa; and the Rio de la Plata in the New World. The obelisk was previously in the Circus Maximus. See where this picture was taken. [?]
